				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$j \in I_2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M30"><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>I</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2020_20593_Article_IEq12.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Then, the projection outlyingness for local shape changes, denoted by LO<sub><italic>j</italic></sub>, can be obtained using Eq. <xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="">3</xref> by taking <inline-formula id="IEq13"><alternatives><tex-math id="M31">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
